  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in chat tool-handler authoring + session persistence.</role>

  <goal>
    `WriteSessionMemoryHandler` lives at `Services/Ai/Handlers/WriteSessionMemoryHandler.cs` implementing `IToolHandler`. Persists session-scoped fact via `ISessionPersistenceService` (extends `ChatSession` with a `SessionFacts[]` collection following the ¬ß11.2 `SaveTabsAsync` pattern, or uses an existing session-fact accessor). `category` enum constrained to: `decision | preference | open-question | assumption`. `confidence` validated 0.0‚Äì1.0. Returns single `ToolResult` with generated `factId`. Unit tests cover happy path, invalid confidence, invalid category, ADR-015 telemetry safety (fact text NEVER logged).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per architecture ¬ß3.1 (T2 lifecycle), ¬ß3.2 (cross-tier separation ‚Äî no auto-promotion to T3), ¬ß8.1 schema. T2 writes are ephemeral to the session ‚Äî promotion to T3 (matter memory) is mediated by `promote_to_matter_memory` (task 088) with explicit user approval per ¬ß6.4. This handler does NOT touch T3.
    </background>
